1. app.config.js
This file stores the web app's Firebase configurations.
Those configurations are from the Firebase website.

2. index.js
- read configurations of cometChat from the app.config file
- use the buildin API from the cometchat to create the app setting
- then initialize the app by appID and appsetting, then render the react app

3. app.js
- import all the component files, also the routers switch route and redirect
- GuardedRoute is to check if the user is authenticated
- useEffect to make sure the user is authenticated
- return the main component by A router switches among GuardedRoute

